1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:02,010
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,640
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:06,510 --> 00:00:09,250
- The person is unavailable...
- This is driving me crazy.

4
00:00:09,650 --> 00:00:10,680
What do we do?

5
00:00:11,750 --> 00:00:13,250
- The person is unavailable...
- Seriously.

6
00:00:13,790 --> 00:00:16,150
Why won't Bucket answer his phone?

7
00:00:16,690 --> 00:00:18,160
I'm going to wring his neck.

8
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:20,830
- Dad.
- Just leave him be.

9
00:00:22,390 --> 00:00:24,500
What if they get into another fight?

10
00:00:24,630 --> 00:00:27,400
If he has reason to fight, let him.
Why must he always just take it?

11
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:29,630
Let's just grill the meat and eat.

12
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:32,940
- What?
- Leave him be. The food's ready.

13
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,010
Just eat.

14
00:00:35,570 --> 00:00:38,280
Uncle. Are you sure you're okay
with not moving?

15
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:39,910
Dong Suk said she's opening a shop.

16
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:42,550
So it's not like
I'll have to see her every day.

17
00:00:43,150 --> 00:00:44,680
But you're in the same neighborhood.

18
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:46,680
What if your stomach hurts
every time you run into her?

19
00:00:47,920 --> 00:00:48,990
Hey.

20
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:50,960
But the funny thing is,

21
00:00:51,420 --> 00:00:53,120
maybe it's because
I thought I was moving.

22
00:00:53,690 --> 00:00:55,390
My stomach didn't hurt
even when we slept together.

23
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:58,060
- What did you just say?
- What did I say?

24
00:00:58,130 --> 00:01:00,060
"My stomach didn't hurt
even when we slept together."

25
00:01:00,870 --> 00:01:01,870
I did?

26
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:05,100
Woo Jae, why is your mind
always in the gutter?

27
00:01:05,170 --> 00:01:06,700
Not "slept together." I meant...

28
00:01:07,970 --> 00:01:09,110
Even when I saw her.

29
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:15,080
- "Saw her?"
- Yes, I meant even when I saw her.

30
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:21,450
So, Dad, you weren't helping me
open a shop for my sake.

31
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:24,320
It was all just a ploy
so he could get on "Human Theater."

32
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:25,390
The person you're calling
is unavailable...

33
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:29,760
Dad. If their family moves,
will you still help me get a shop?

34
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:32,600
I always keep my word.

35
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:35,330
- You heard him, right?
- Yes.

36
00:01:35,430 --> 00:01:36,900
Pick up, Se Ri.
Please, just pick up.

37
00:01:37,540 --> 00:01:39,740
Why isn't she answering?

38
00:01:40,470 --> 00:01:42,670
But how did that letter
end up with our stepmom?

39
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:43,980
Dad, you gave it to her?

40
00:01:43,980 --> 00:01:45,310
- The person you're calling...
- I did.

41
00:01:45,810 --> 00:01:48,880
- But I gave it to Seong Mi.
- That explains it.

42
00:01:49,150 --> 00:01:51,420
She must have passed it on to her.

43
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:55,190
Seriously, Dad, why do you
always have to complicate things?

44
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:58,560
- This is all your fault, you brat.
- How is this my fault?

45
00:01:58,620 --> 00:01:59,920
You're the one
who told me to write the letter.

46
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:02,130
You asked me
to come up with a plan for you.

47
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:03,830
See? What did I tell you?

48
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,000
I told you to come clean
before you got caught, didn't I?

49
00:02:06,970 --> 00:02:09,900
Aunt must have been really upset.
To think she actually ran away.

50
00:02:10,130 --> 00:02:13,440
Of course. She managed
family matters by herself,

51
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:15,970
so to be completely left out
of something this big...

52
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:17,710
The sense of betrayal
must be overwhelming.

53
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:22,780
You don't think
she's gone for good, do you?

54
00:02:23,180 --> 00:02:24,520
Go find her and bring her back. Now!

55
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:27,950
I'm seriously going to lose my mind.

56
00:02:29,820 --> 00:02:33,590
Hey, Bucket!
Why didn't you answer my call?

57
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,160
What are you doing here?

58
00:02:35,230 --> 00:02:38,700
You jerk! You really have to ask?
Why were you meeting with Seong Mi?

59
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:42,530
Look, I'm not in my right mind
right now, so just go.

60
00:02:43,270 --> 00:02:46,440
You jerk! Do I look like
I'm in my right mind?

61
00:02:48,740 --> 00:02:49,870
Hey, but...

62
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:52,510
I'm the one who gave Seong Mi
that letter.

63
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,850
- But why did it...
- What, you jerk?

64
00:02:55,580 --> 00:02:59,050
- You gave the letter to Seong Mi?
- Don't change the subject, jerk.

65
00:02:59,350 --> 00:03:00,950
I'm asking
why it ended up with Se Ri!

66
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:04,660
How should I know?
You've got some nerve, blaming me.

67
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,520
Dad, that's enough.

68
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:08,730
Father, that's enough. All right?

69
00:03:09,060 --> 00:03:10,400
When did you get here? Move.

70
00:03:11,100 --> 00:03:14,500
Hey! Why did you meet my Seong Mi
and spill everything?

71
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:17,440
You didn't get your way,
so you decided to burn it all down?

72
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:18,840
You're the one who went back
on your word!

73
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:22,740
You were so fickle. I was trying
to bring you to your senses!

74
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:24,640
And how did that work out for you?

75
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:27,110
You should've kept your mouth shut!

76
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:29,710
You shouldn't have butted in
and made such a mess of things.

77
00:03:29,850 --> 00:03:34,290
- Dad, please. I'm so sorry.
- You're the one who backed out!

78
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:38,820
- How can a person be so fickle?
- So I can't change my mind?

79
00:03:39,220 --> 00:03:42,230
- That's it. I'm moving!
- Fine, go.

80
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:44,030
- That's right. I'm leaving.
- Then go!

81
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:45,100
I said, I'm leaving!

82
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,670
- Let's go, Dad. All right?
- Let's go, Dad.

83
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:50,900
Hey, I'm moving out tomorrow
so I never have to see you again.

84
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,470
Fine, go then, you jerk!
Leave tomorrow!

85
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:56,270
- Nothing's been right since we met.
- Stop it.

86
00:03:56,410 --> 00:03:57,410
Leave first thing tomorrow.

87
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:01,350
The same goes for me, you jerk!
You punk, what are you kicking?

88
00:04:01,410 --> 00:04:03,750
If you don't move,
I'll throw you out myself.

89
00:04:04,050 --> 00:04:05,920
- Go, you jerk. Just go!
- Dad.

90
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:07,150
Please.

91
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:10,360
- You rotten punk. Move tomorrow!
- Let's go.

92
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,020
Why, you little... I can't even...

93
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:14,030
For crying out loud.

94
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:19,500
What was all that about?

95
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:23,200
Your stepmom is gone, Hyun Bin.

96
00:04:24,070 --> 00:04:25,070
What?

97
00:04:25,570 --> 00:04:26,870
Behind Se Ri's back,

98
00:04:27,740 --> 00:04:30,070
I tried to stop Jeong Han's family
from moving, and she found out.

99
00:04:31,810 --> 00:04:33,480
What do you mean
you tried to stop them?

100
00:04:34,410 --> 00:04:35,910
I was going to tell her tomorrow,

101
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:38,580
but it looks like
she already found out.

102
00:04:39,980 --> 00:04:41,020
Hold on a second.

103
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:45,790
She's not picking up
your calls either, right?

104
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:47,960
The person you're trying to reach
is unavailable...

105
00:04:48,960 --> 00:04:51,130
What about tracking her location?

106
00:04:51,530 --> 00:04:52,530
She turned it off.

107
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,070
She turned everything off
and just vanished.

108
00:04:57,800 --> 00:04:58,970
What am I supposed to do now?

109
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:02,810
When you decided to do this,
didn't you think this might happen?

110
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,210
I didn't.

111
00:05:06,210 --> 00:05:09,710
I thought no matter what I did,
Se Ri would always stay by my side.

112
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:13,990
Who in the world sticks by someone
no matter what they do?

113
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:15,420
People get divorced
over the smallest things,

114
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:17,460
and parents even abandon
their own kids these days.

115
00:05:18,090 --> 00:05:19,090
Am I...

116
00:05:19,790 --> 00:05:20,990
being abandoned again?

117
00:05:23,230 --> 00:05:24,530
What am I really going to do?

118
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:27,370
You crazy fool.

119
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:29,800
You darn fool.

120
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,770
Dad, what are you doing?
Seriously, how is this helping?

121
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:37,310
No, I deserve this. I'm such a fool.

122
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:41,710
- I'm a fool!
- Dad, please stop!

123
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:45,480
You crazy fool.

124
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:54,960
- That Bucket guy, I swear...
- Dad.

125
00:05:56,190 --> 00:05:59,160
Did you ask Mom out just to tell her
you weren't moving?

126
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,400
I did.

127
00:06:01,130 --> 00:06:03,940
Dad, seriously...
What is wrong with you?

128
00:06:04,270 --> 00:06:05,740
That's enough, okay?

129
00:06:05,740 --> 00:06:08,270
Everyone's been yelling at me,
and I'm at my wits' end.

130
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:11,480
So you went to Dr. Yang's house
to take it out on him?

131
00:06:11,740 --> 00:06:14,780
Take it out on him?
I was angry because he deserved it.

132
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:17,520
And you. Weren't you supposed
to pick up lettuce?

133
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,020
Why were you over there
with that guy?

134
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:22,050
And what's with this bouquet?
What is this?

135
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,560
This is...

136
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,890
A junior colleague from work
gave it to me.

137
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:30,160
Director Yang just gave me a ride
since we were heading the same way,

138
00:06:30,230 --> 00:06:32,100
and we just stopped
to talk for a second.

139
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,700
And he's the director.
Why are you calling him "that guy?"

140
00:06:34,930 --> 00:06:36,970
He's your director, not mine.

141
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:38,840
And back there,

142
00:06:39,140 --> 00:06:41,840
why did you apologize
to that jerk, Bucket?

143
00:06:41,910 --> 00:06:44,980
So what, I should've taken your side
and fought with Director Yang?

144
00:06:45,540 --> 00:06:48,580
Dad, seriously,
what is your problem?

145
00:06:49,010 --> 00:06:52,080
Are you allergic to getting along
with Mom or something?

146
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,520
Allergic? Don't be ridiculous...

147
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:58,260
That reminds me. Hey, Ju Ah.
Gong Ju Ah.

148
00:06:58,660 --> 00:06:59,720
What now?

149
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:02,490
You need to talk to Woo Jae.

150
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,660
Woo Jae? What's wrong with him now?

151
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,200
Well, look at you.

152
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,740
Just go live in the lettuce fields.
Why are you back already?

153
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:18,340
Did you hear about
all the drama at home?

154
00:07:19,010 --> 00:07:21,780
Did I hear about it?
Dad grabbed Dr. Yang by the collar,

155
00:07:21,850 --> 00:07:23,050
and I was the one
who had to drag him home.

156
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,320
Seriously?

157
00:07:25,220 --> 00:07:28,790
What are we going to do?
How's Mom? Did you talk to her?

158
00:07:28,950 --> 00:07:31,360
Forget about that.
Dad told me something.

159
00:07:31,690 --> 00:07:32,720
Are you on medication?

160
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:37,030
I can't believe Dad told you that
now of all times.

161
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:40,460
You should have told me
if something like that was going on.

162
00:07:40,670 --> 00:07:42,630
Don't worry about it. It's nothing.

163
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,200
Is this why you said you wanted...

164
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,100
to take a break from studying
and get a job?

165
00:07:47,170 --> 00:07:51,310
This is insane.
If you quit too, Mom will lose it.

166
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:54,350
Don't worry. I'm not like you.

167
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:58,180
How are you any different?
I had an anxiety disorder, too.

168
00:07:58,220 --> 00:07:59,250
Don't you remember?

169
00:07:59,350 --> 00:08:02,520
You didn't want to be a doctor.
I'm like this because I do.

170
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:04,990
Gong Woo Jae.

171
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:09,630
Live the life you want,
not the one Mom wants for you.

172
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:13,330
Okay.

173
00:08:14,070 --> 00:08:15,800
Once Mom is doing a little better,

174
00:08:17,270 --> 00:08:18,570
I'll come clean about everything.

175
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,310
Seriously...

176
00:08:28,210 --> 00:08:29,310
I'm home.

177
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:34,750
- Hyun Bin!
- Did you find Se Ri?

178
00:08:35,220 --> 00:08:38,020
No. She's not picking up,
and her car is gone.

179
00:08:38,660 --> 00:08:39,690
What are we going to do?

180
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:41,430
Father.

181
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:43,930
I think I've been abandoned again.

182
00:08:45,030 --> 00:08:46,330
I think she's going to divorce me.

183
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:48,630
Divorce? Over something like this?

184
00:08:49,170 --> 00:08:50,230
There's no way.

185
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:54,070
What do you mean, "no way?"
In her shoes, I'd want a divorce.

186
00:08:54,310 --> 00:08:57,610
I can understand Eun Bin acting out,
but you let it happen, Grandfather.

187
00:08:57,810 --> 00:09:01,180
How could you just stand by
and let it get this bad?

188
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:05,480
If she'll get a divorce over this,
then let her.

189
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:08,620
If that's all we mean to her,
good riddance!

190
00:09:08,690 --> 00:09:12,420
Hey, will you shut it?
This was all your doing, wasn't it?

191
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:14,930
I can't believe you.

192
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:18,760
Anyway, all of you need to think
about what you've done.

193
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:23,530
Dr. Gong's family is moving
as planned. Just know that.

194
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:25,470
Dad.

195
00:09:28,470 --> 00:09:29,940
I can't deal with this.

196
00:09:31,380 --> 00:09:34,680
Dad, what if
she really doesn't come back?

197
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:45,990
Do you have any idea
where she might have gone?

198
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,630
A friend's place, maybe?

199
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,730
She doesn't have any friends.

200
00:09:52,130 --> 00:09:53,800
She's not close
with the other doctors' wives...

201
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,630
And she's not the type
to air our dirty laundry.

202
00:09:56,970 --> 00:10:00,740
She grew up in an orphanage,
so she has no blood relatives.

203
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:04,440
Her whole adult life,

204
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:06,610
she worked at a salon,

205
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:09,410
then got pushed into a pageant.
That's where we met.

206
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:12,450
No friends, no relatives,

207
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:16,150
nowhere to go,
and nothing to her name.

208
00:10:18,990 --> 00:10:23,360
I said a wedding was embarrassing,
so we'd just register the marriage.

209
00:10:24,730 --> 00:10:27,160
I told her I didn't believe in love,
so she should just raise the kids,

210
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:30,670
take care of my father,
and run the house.

211
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,840
And even after all that,
Se Ri still chose to be with me.

212
00:10:36,110 --> 00:10:39,480
What did I do to a woman like that?
Hyun Bin, what have I done?

213
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:56,990
Day one of our relationship,
and it's already been a rough ride.

214
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:05,470
- Yes, Director.
- Come on, "Director?" We're dating.

215
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:09,570
My gosh,
what should I call you then?

216
00:11:10,570 --> 00:11:11,910
Just say, "Hyun Bin."

217
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:15,510
- I can't.
- "Mr. Hyun Bin," then?

218
00:11:16,050 --> 00:11:17,050
No, I can't.

219
00:11:17,580 --> 00:11:20,220
- Yes, you can.
- No, I can't.

220
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:24,560
I'm worried it'll become a habit.
What if I say it in front of others?

221
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:26,220
All right.

222
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:30,190
Then we can discuss it later.

223
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:34,770
By the way,
has your mom come home yet?

224
00:11:35,900 --> 00:11:39,840
Not yet. By the way,
is Dr. Han doing any better?

225
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:43,540
She's locked her door
and won't come out.

226
00:11:44,680 --> 00:11:45,680
Oh, dear.

227
00:11:46,680 --> 00:11:50,650
When your mother gets back,
please tell her we're moving out.

228
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:51,920
I will.

229
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:56,920
Wow, our first day is really off
to a rough start, isn't it?

230
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:58,860
Tell me about it.

231
00:12:00,620 --> 00:12:02,860
Hey, no sighing.

232
00:12:03,130 --> 00:12:05,760
Especially after we pinky-promised
not to let things get to us.

233
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:08,000
You're right.

234
00:12:09,130 --> 00:12:12,270
Man, hearing your voice
really makes me miss you.

235
00:12:12,870 --> 00:12:14,110
Should I come over?

236
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,840
Let's just see each other tomorrow.
Tomorrow. Okay?

237
00:12:17,610 --> 00:12:18,940
Okay, I'll let you go then.

238
00:12:19,410 --> 00:12:21,350
See you tomorrow. Sleep well.

239
00:12:29,020 --> 00:12:30,020
What?

240
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,990
Stepmother?

241
00:12:35,630 --> 00:12:37,230
You've been calling.

242
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:39,500
I was driving.

243
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:41,800
It would've been dangerous
to answer.

244
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:45,070
Right. I'm at my dad's house now.
I heard everything.

245
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,570
Where are you, by the way?

246
00:12:50,980 --> 00:12:52,040
On a little staycation.

247
00:12:52,810 --> 00:12:54,250
I just needed some time alone.

248
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:58,280
I see. In that case, go wild
with Grandfather's credit card,

249
00:12:58,450 --> 00:13:02,590
and get some good rest.
I'll give them an earful for you.

250
00:13:03,220 --> 00:13:05,320
Okay. Thanks.

251
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:39,090
Who's there?

252
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:42,660
- Sister?
- My gosh, Stella!

253
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,060
Is that really you, Stella?

254
00:13:48,270 --> 00:13:53,040
It really is you. What brings you
out here, especially at this hour?

255
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:58,480
- Did I startle you by showing up?
- No, it's great to see you.

256
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:01,580
I've actually been thinking
about you a lot lately.

257
00:14:02,110 --> 00:14:05,720
The Lord knew what was in my heart
and guided you here.

258
00:14:07,380 --> 00:14:08,950
I've missed you, Sister.

259
00:14:29,610 --> 00:14:33,280
- Mother.
- Hey. Did you get some sleep?

260
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:37,180
Gosh, did you wake up early
to make this for me?

261
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,320
What?

262
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:41,220
No, I was just making it for myself.

263
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:44,790
But you made far more than you could
possibly eat alone, didn't you?

264
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:47,260
Yes.

265
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:56,030
Here, drink water first, then eat.
Your throat must be parched.

266
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:06,840
You didn't have dinner either,
did you, Mother?

267
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:10,650
Of course not. How could I eat
when you are on a hunger strike?

268
00:15:10,710 --> 00:15:11,820
Do you think I'd have any appetite?

269
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:15,050
We're both being punished
for my good-for-nothing son.

270
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:20,690
- How is any of this your fault?
- I swear, I didn't know.

271
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,130
I wasn't in on it.

272
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,160
I know.

273
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,070
What's wrong?

274
00:15:36,740 --> 00:15:38,610
Have you lost your appetite?

275
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:40,410
No.

276
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:43,510
I can't eat it.
It just doesn't taste good.

277
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:45,480
For crying out loud.

278
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:48,520
Nobody in the world
would ever believe it.

279
00:15:48,890 --> 00:15:52,460
That the esteemed Dr. Han Seong Mi
insults her mother-in-law's cooking.

280
00:16:06,000 --> 00:16:07,300
You know something?

281
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,640
Are you talking in your sleep,
or are you talking to me?

282
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:15,680
Se Ri kept trying to convince me.

283
00:16:17,150 --> 00:16:19,180
She begged me
not to send you to study abroad.

284
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,690
She said
she'd raise you well herself.

285
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:25,190
I know.

286
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,930
That's the kind of woman she is.

287
00:16:32,660 --> 00:16:33,930
Just get some more sleep.

288
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,170
Eun Bin, you're not asleep?

289
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:47,040
Hyun Bin,
our stepmom still hasn't come home.

290
00:16:47,610 --> 00:16:50,580
I've called her dozens of times
and sent her countless texts.

291
00:16:50,650 --> 00:16:51,920
How could she do this to us?

292
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,180
I bet she wouldn't do this
if I were her own daughter.

293
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:58,520
A real daughter
wouldn't make trouble like you do.

294
00:16:59,090 --> 00:17:02,690
You don't think Dad will divorce her
because of me, do you?

295
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:05,800
Goodness.
You should've treated her better.

296
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,170
Is Grandpa still asleep?

297
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:11,540
- He left a while ago.
- He left?

298
00:17:27,790 --> 00:17:30,690
Hey! I told you I'd handle it.
What is with you, seriously?

299
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:33,190
- Go on, go.
- Hold on. Hey, what the...

300
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:36,630
Listen, the second you walk in,
you get down on your knees. Got it?

301
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:39,830
Get on my knees? What for?
Was what I did really that bad?

302
00:17:39,830 --> 00:17:43,100
- Yes, you messed up badly. Knock.
- Hey, but...

303
00:17:45,570 --> 00:17:47,000
This is ridiculous.

304
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:54,410
Hey, Seong Mi! Han Seong Mi!

305
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:56,050
Honestly... Give me a break.

306
00:17:56,310 --> 00:18:00,820
- Gently. Be sweet.
- Seriously. This is nuts.

307
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:10,760
- Seong Mi. Are you awake?
- Gosh, just open it. Hurry up.

308
00:18:11,130 --> 00:18:13,100
- What if it's locked?
- Dad, come on...

309
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,470
- Dad!
- Please!

310
00:18:21,910 --> 00:18:24,370
- It's unlocked. Yes.
- It is?

311
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:26,480
- So, you go in.
- What?

312
00:18:26,740 --> 00:18:28,450
Get on your knees, quick!

313
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:34,620
Seong Mi.

314
00:18:35,550 --> 00:18:38,460
I really messed up this time.
All right?

315
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:42,530
Please, just let it slide this once.
Seong Mi, I'm serious.

316
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:44,430
Please...

317
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,900
Seong Mi.

318
00:18:47,830 --> 00:18:48,830
What?

319
00:18:49,330 --> 00:18:51,840
Seong Mi!

320
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,840
What?

321
00:18:57,010 --> 00:18:58,510
So, is Mom not coming out?

322
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:01,910
She's gone.

323
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:06,180
Wait, don't tell me...
She ran away from home?

324
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:09,090
Hey! Don't be ridiculous.
She didn't run away!

325
00:19:09,150 --> 00:19:12,560
This is why you should've apologized
last night.

326
00:19:12,690 --> 00:19:15,130
She locked the door
and wouldn't answer,

327
00:19:15,130 --> 00:19:17,560
no matter how many times I knocked.
What was I supposed to do?

328
00:19:20,860 --> 00:19:22,970
Grandma's not here either.

329
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:24,640
What?

330
00:20:00,870 --> 00:20:04,470
So? It's better
than the porridge you make, right?

331
00:20:05,310 --> 00:20:06,340
I suppose it is.

332
00:20:07,180 --> 00:20:09,050
I can't tell if it tastes good
because someone else made it,

333
00:20:09,110 --> 00:20:12,280
or because we're eating by the sea
for the first time in a while.

334
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:18,490
Are you buying me this big meal
before breaking some news?

335
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:21,960
What? You want to divorce Jeong Han
or something?

336
00:20:51,420 --> 00:20:52,490
Stella.

337
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,760
Are you sure
it's okay for you to be here?

338
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:59,100
Your husband was suspicious
and started tracking your location.

339
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,400
You couldn't visit after that,
could you?

340
00:21:03,370 --> 00:21:04,530
The location tracking...

341
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:06,870
I turned it off.

342
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,410
Is something wrong?

343
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:12,040
Don't tell me
you're not planning on going home.

344
00:21:20,780 --> 00:21:21,790
Sister.

345
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,660
I have a favor to ask you.

346
00:21:29,630 --> 00:21:30,790
Just eat what's here.

347
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:33,430
You've eaten like royalty
each morning for over a decade.

348
00:21:33,430 --> 00:21:35,730
It won't kill you to eat like this
for one day.

349
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:39,170
But we don't know
if it's 1 day, 2, or even 3.

350
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:44,270
Go down to the police station
and file a missing person's report.

351
00:21:44,540 --> 00:21:46,740
What? Grandfather, come on.

352
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:49,780
This is so annoying! There aren't
any clean towels in the bathroom!

353
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:52,520
I put the laundry out ages ago.
Unbelievable.

354
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:58,290
- Look at the state of you!
- What?

355
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,860
Dad, why come out
while you're shaving?

356
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:02,690
At least wipe your face.

357
00:22:03,430 --> 00:22:08,070
- I did?
- Did Stepmom always help you shave?

358
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,930
What? Hey.

359
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,800
Does anyone know
where my underwear is?

360
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:15,810
Dad, have you lost your mind?

361
00:22:16,170 --> 00:22:19,880
This is exactly why you need to
report her missing and find her.

362
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:23,080
We'll look for her after we eat.
Here, hurry up and eat. Eat.

363
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,720
And what are you going to do
when you find her?

364
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:28,350
Ask her to cook for you, do laundry,
and shave your face for you?

365
00:22:29,050 --> 00:22:33,420
Does anyone here even know
what our stepmom's favorite food is?

366
00:22:35,430 --> 00:22:38,860
Now that you mention it,
I don't think I know either.

367
00:22:39,860 --> 00:22:42,630
Her meals were just tasting the food
as she cooked.

368
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:45,370
And she'd eat some of the leftovers
while cleaning up.

369
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:49,270
How can you all be so awful?

370
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:52,910
She's only been gone for one day,
and the house is already a mess.

371
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:57,650
How can you leave her out
of such an important decision?

372
00:22:58,150 --> 00:23:02,390
He's right. I'd feel left out, too.

373
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:04,590
If she comes back,

374
00:23:05,220 --> 00:23:06,460
I swear I'll change.

375
00:23:07,390 --> 00:23:08,490
You really mean that?

376
00:23:08,890 --> 00:23:09,930
Of course, I do.

377
00:23:11,030 --> 00:23:14,160
- Will you change, Grandfather?
- Yes!

378
00:23:14,930 --> 00:23:15,930
Eun Bin, what about you?

379
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:21,140
You know where she is, don't you?

380
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:24,010
Where is she? Is she okay?

381
00:23:24,340 --> 00:23:26,680
Is she coming back?
Is she coming home?

382
00:23:27,610 --> 00:23:30,910
She's okay, but I'm not sure
if she'll come back.

383
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:38,520
But if she does decide to come back,

384
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:41,730
every one of you needs to change.
Got it?

385
00:23:58,580 --> 00:23:59,840
(Father-in-law)

386
00:23:59,940 --> 00:24:04,150
What can I do to make it up to you?
Just tell me.

387
00:24:06,280 --> 00:24:07,980
The house feels so empty
without you.

388
00:24:08,690 --> 00:24:10,020
Please come back.

389
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:13,690
I understand why you're upset.

390
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:17,230
This is enough. Please come back.
You're killing my brother.

391
00:24:20,660 --> 00:24:23,770
I'm sorry for being so mean to you
on purpose.

392
00:24:24,130 --> 00:24:27,940
I'll be good from now on.
Please come back. Please?

393
00:24:30,570 --> 00:24:32,210
(My Dr. Yang)

394
00:24:32,210 --> 00:24:33,240
I'm sorry, Se Ri.

395
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:36,380
From now on, I'll never do anything
you don't want me to.

396
00:24:36,950 --> 00:24:39,120
I swear on my love for you.

397
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:54,030
Judging by your expression,
I don't have to worry.

398
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,000
That's right.

399
00:24:59,170 --> 00:25:00,170
I think...

400
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,540
I'm doing all right.

401
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:10,350
But...

402
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:15,790
I'm not the only one doing okay,
am I, Sister?

403
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:37,070
Mother. You're not disappointed...

404
00:25:37,770 --> 00:25:39,110
that I'm more successful
than your son?

405
00:25:39,780 --> 00:25:41,010
My goodness.

406
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:45,650
What in the world
are you talking about?

407
00:25:48,180 --> 00:25:51,350
I took out loans and even used
my brother-in-law's deposit...

408
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:53,890
just to open my own clinic in Seoul.

409
00:25:54,420 --> 00:25:58,130
And now, I'm on TV,
shooting commercials and modeling.

410
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,330
You're not upset about any of that?

411
00:26:02,430 --> 00:26:06,240
Someone at the market did ask
if I was getting dementia.

412
00:26:06,970 --> 00:26:10,140
They wondered why I'd give it all
to my daughter-in-law, not my son.

413
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,910
Exactly!

414
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:14,510
What mother-in-law would do that
for her daughter-in-law?

415
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,750
How could I be your mother-in-law?
I'm your mother.

416
00:26:19,450 --> 00:26:23,890
When your grandma passed,
I made her a solemn promise.

417
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:28,160
That I'd raise you as my daughter
so she wouldn't have to worry.

418
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:31,590
That's why you're my daughter.

419
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:35,470
If you divorce Jeong Han,
you can come and live with me.

420
00:26:37,870 --> 00:26:40,500
Should I really divorce him?

421
00:26:40,970 --> 00:26:42,970
Should I divorce him
and just live with you?

422
00:26:43,870 --> 00:26:45,110
If you want to, go ahead.

423
00:26:45,710 --> 00:26:46,910
I won't stop you.

424
00:26:48,850 --> 00:26:51,610
You're saying that because you know
I can't do it, aren't you?

425
00:26:52,150 --> 00:26:53,350
What? Why not?

426
00:26:53,580 --> 00:26:57,590
What, is there some rule that says
a family counselor can't divorce?

427
00:26:58,150 --> 00:27:01,390
By that logic,
can doctors not get sick?

428
00:27:01,830 --> 00:27:04,290
And schoolteachers' kids
all have to be straight-A students?

429
00:27:06,030 --> 00:27:09,600
Wow, that abalone porridge
really lit a fire under you.

430
00:27:11,170 --> 00:27:12,200
Or...

431
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:16,910
Let's leave Jeong Han in Onjeong
and move away, just the two of us.

432
00:27:27,950 --> 00:27:29,790
What's upsetting you the most?

433
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:33,120
Go on, tell me.
We can bad-mouth my son.

434
00:27:35,860 --> 00:27:38,060
I saw Dr. Yang yesterday,

435
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:42,930
and he said I don't understand
my husband's feelings.

436
00:27:44,130 --> 00:27:45,170
The nerve of that guy.

437
00:27:45,900 --> 00:27:49,340
He should be confiding in his wife.
He's so nosy...

438
00:27:50,510 --> 00:27:53,840
But the thing is,
I knew how Jeong Han felt.

439
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:59,580
But I liked that he was doing
what I wanted.

440
00:28:00,280 --> 00:28:04,920
And here I am, someone who
reads hearts and prescribes love,

441
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,460
yet I pretended not to understand
what my own husband was feeling.

442
00:28:10,830 --> 00:28:12,300
I was so ashamed of myself.

443
00:28:32,450 --> 00:28:35,220
Yes, thank you.
I'll really enjoy this.

444
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,720
What?

445
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:39,360
Officer Jung,
you're out grocery shopping too.

446
00:28:39,620 --> 00:28:41,490
Yes. It's my day off.

447
00:28:42,490 --> 00:28:44,660
Wait, why the long face?

448
00:28:45,630 --> 00:28:50,500
Dr. Gong changed his mind.
He says they're moving after all.

449
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:56,270
He changes his mind so often,
I can't keep track anymore.

450
00:28:56,810 --> 00:28:57,810
Hang on a second.

451
00:28:58,370 --> 00:28:59,380
So then,

452
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:02,010
what does that mean for you,
Nurse Oh?

453
00:29:02,710 --> 00:29:05,120
I think I'm just going to
take some time off.

454
00:29:08,180 --> 00:29:11,960
I guess I won't be seeing you around
as much then.

455
00:29:12,660 --> 00:29:16,790
I live nearby, so I'll come here
to get groceries from time to time.

456
00:29:18,090 --> 00:29:19,400
I should get going.

457
00:29:20,130 --> 00:29:21,130
Okay.

458
00:29:31,070 --> 00:29:32,280
Sauce on the side or all over?

459
00:29:33,610 --> 00:29:36,210
- The drench-and-sog.
- What's that?

460
00:29:36,850 --> 00:29:39,220
Here, watch. Like this.

461
00:29:39,450 --> 00:29:42,990
You drench it, and then eat it
when it gets soggy.

462
00:29:44,350 --> 00:29:46,360
See? I knew
we had the same taste in food.

463
00:29:50,760 --> 00:29:52,260
Get nice and soggy.

464
00:29:54,530 --> 00:29:57,670
You know why I got shot down
on that blind date?

465
00:29:58,700 --> 00:30:02,010
So Hye's brother just has bad taste?
Not that I'm complaining.

466
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,740
No, our tastes in food
were just way too different.

467
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:10,010
He was cutting fat off
the pork belly with scissors.

468
00:30:10,080 --> 00:30:13,480
What? Seriously?
That's basically a crime, isn't it?

469
00:30:13,580 --> 00:30:14,880
Lock him up.

470
00:30:15,850 --> 00:30:18,660
On top of that, he doesn't drink.
And get this.

471
00:30:18,720 --> 00:30:23,160
- He doesn't eat carbs either.
- What? He deserves a life sentence.

472
00:30:28,730 --> 00:30:31,330
Why didn't your blind date work out,
Director?

473
00:30:32,470 --> 00:30:35,000
It wasn't a blind date.
She was just...

474
00:30:35,240 --> 00:30:37,810
someone I know
through my stepmother.

475
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:43,650
Your stepmother...
She wants you to get married?

476
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:48,590
Yes. She thinks if I get married,
then I'll decide to stay in Korea.

477
00:30:52,290 --> 00:30:54,960
Hurry up and eat.
We have somewhere to go after this.

478
00:30:56,130 --> 00:30:57,130
Okay.

479
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,760
This looks delicious.

480
00:31:00,830 --> 00:31:02,700
(3H Acupressure Beds)

481
00:31:03,970 --> 00:31:05,240
Welcome.

482
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:12,240
Why are we here?
Shopping for our first home?

483
00:31:12,540 --> 00:31:13,540
What?

484
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:18,920
I'm kidding. Why the big eyes?
We're a couple, so what?

485
00:31:18,980 --> 00:31:21,650
You really got me there.
You totally threw me off.

486
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:24,890
Seriously, though,
why did you bring me here?

487
00:31:25,390 --> 00:31:29,190
When my stepmother returns,
I want them to be like newlyweds,

488
00:31:29,260 --> 00:31:30,560
so I thought I'd get them a new bed.

489
00:31:32,730 --> 00:31:34,730
They've got quite a selection here.

490
00:31:35,530 --> 00:31:38,100
- Please, try it out.
- Should I?

491
00:31:38,770 --> 00:31:39,770
Sure.

492
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:42,270
Come.

493
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:46,280
(3H Acupressure Beds)

494
00:31:47,980 --> 00:31:49,250
This one's nice.

495
00:31:49,910 --> 00:31:51,350
It really is.

496
00:31:52,620 --> 00:31:54,720
I thought I'd throw a little party
for my mom when she comes.

497
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,720
You know,
a little welcome home event.

498
00:31:56,820 --> 00:31:59,620
A party? Do you have any good ideas?

499
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:04,330
(Party and Event Supply Kits)

500
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:06,200
This is it.

501
00:32:09,970 --> 00:32:10,970
Ta-da!

502
00:32:12,140 --> 00:32:15,570
A real-life princess!
For you, Princess.

503
00:32:16,340 --> 00:32:17,910
- How do I look?
- The star of the show, Gong Ju Ah.

504
00:32:17,910 --> 00:32:19,110
Princess Gong Ju Ah.

505
00:32:19,180 --> 00:32:20,980
- Ta-da!
- Oh, right there.

506
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:22,850
Here.

507
00:32:37,860 --> 00:32:38,860
What?

508
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:42,170
I said I'm so happy,
it feels like I'm dreaming.

509
00:32:43,570 --> 00:32:47,240
Right, I had a dream that you were
planning a surprise event for me.

510
00:32:47,740 --> 00:32:49,710
Me, in your dream?
I was planning an event?

511
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:54,510
I've got a great idea.

512
00:33:18,670 --> 00:33:21,570
<i>I'm on top of the world</i>

513
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:25,040
<i>With the woman who loves me</i>

514
00:33:25,510 --> 00:33:28,080
<i>With my Cha Se Ri</i>

515
00:33:28,580 --> 00:33:33,480
<i>I want to walk my own path,</i>
<i>I really do</i>

516
00:33:46,660 --> 00:33:47,730
So, how's it going?

517
00:33:48,300 --> 00:33:50,800
You studied abroad. This is the best
you could come up with?

518
00:33:50,870 --> 00:33:53,600
Shoot, they said this would work.
That it's every woman's fantasy.

519
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:56,170
Hey, who told you that?
This is too cringe-worthy to watch.

520
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:58,170
Aunt does not look impressed.

521
00:34:00,140 --> 00:34:02,950
<i>I have been so lonely</i>
<i>and had such a hard time</i>

522
00:34:03,050 --> 00:34:06,520
<i>But it's only a rehearsal</i>

523
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:10,450
<i>I'm not going to fall down</i>

524
00:34:10,590 --> 00:34:13,020
<i>We got this</i>

525
00:34:15,090 --> 00:34:16,160
I'm sorry, Se Ri.

526
00:34:16,890 --> 00:34:19,430
I'll never make you
feel lonely again...

527
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,530
Honey.

528
00:34:22,130 --> 00:34:26,000
- Se Ri, I'm sorry.
- Honey.

529
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,500
I love you.

530
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:46,390
One, two, three!

531
00:34:47,090 --> 00:34:49,090
- Ta-da!
- Ta-da!

532
00:34:49,260 --> 00:34:54,760
(We're sorry.)

533
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:04,040
- We're sorry.
- We're so sorry.

534
00:35:17,790 --> 00:35:21,120
- Han Seong Mi!
- Han Seong Mi!

535
00:35:21,190 --> 00:35:25,530
- Han Seong Mi!
- Han Seong Mi!

536
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:42,950
<i>The single, clear tear in your eye</i>

537
00:35:43,850 --> 00:35:47,580
<i>Makes my heart pound</i>

538
00:35:47,850 --> 00:35:51,690
<i>It pounds</i>

539
00:35:52,620 --> 00:35:54,990
<i>- Thump, thump, thump</i>
<i>- Thump, thump, thump</i>

540
00:35:55,290 --> 00:35:57,590
<i>- You are my personal IV drip</i>
<i>- You are my personal IV drip</i>

541
00:35:57,590 --> 00:36:00,660
<i>- My very own intravenous shot</i>
<i>- My very own intravenous shot</i>

542
00:36:00,760 --> 00:36:05,640
<i>- You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>
<i>- You're the cure for my arrhythmia</i>

543
00:36:05,740 --> 00:36:07,500
<i>- You are my IV drip</i>
<i>- You are my IV drip</i>

544
00:36:07,500 --> 00:36:10,270
<i>- My personal Band-Aid</i>
<i>- My personal Band-Aid</i>

545
00:36:10,610 --> 00:36:15,040
<i>- You heal all my wounds</i>
<i>- You heal all my wounds</i>

546
00:36:18,580 --> 00:36:22,350
Hey, Seong Mi.

547
00:36:24,190 --> 00:36:25,290
You.

548
00:36:26,190 --> 00:36:27,190
Let's talk inside.

549
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:41,500
- Grandma, is Mom still mad?
- Does Mom...

550
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:43,070
really want a divorce?

551
00:36:50,210 --> 00:36:51,650
(The Cutest Ever)

552
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:56,690
We'll move. All right?

553
00:36:57,950 --> 00:37:00,490
Come on, stop being so mad,
Seong Mi.

554
00:37:01,590 --> 00:37:03,490
Do you really mean that?

555
00:37:03,930 --> 00:37:08,430
Yes, I do. I've already called
the hospitals to refer my patients,

556
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:12,540
and the senior companion service...
I took care of it all.

557
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:15,910
See? Even now, you're listing
your actions and duties...

558
00:37:16,070 --> 00:37:18,340
just to protect your own ego.

559
00:37:18,910 --> 00:37:22,380
Hey, why do you have to
analyze everything?

560
00:37:22,980 --> 00:37:25,750
Why can't you just tell me
how you really feel?

561
00:37:26,380 --> 00:37:29,850
Why do I have to hear how you feel
from other people?

562
00:37:29,990 --> 00:37:32,320
Why do you keep making me out
to be the bad guy?

563
00:37:32,820 --> 00:37:36,190
This is classic
passive-aggressive behavior.

564
00:37:37,290 --> 00:37:39,130
What? How am I being...

565
00:37:41,130 --> 00:37:42,160
Tell me.

566
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:44,370
Tell me why you had second thoughts.

567
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:49,670
Please, just tell me.

568
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:51,140
Please? Honey.

569
00:38:00,150 --> 00:38:02,050
I had a job interview,

570
00:38:02,620 --> 00:38:04,220
and I was a little scared.

571
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:08,620
I guess it's because
I've been in Onjeong for so long.

572
00:38:09,790 --> 00:38:11,790
I started wondering
if I could adapt to somewhere new,

573
00:38:12,730 --> 00:38:16,530
if I could even pull my own weight
at my age.

574
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,070
Those thoughts
just made me feel a bit...

575
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:20,800
I got scared.

576
00:38:24,770 --> 00:38:27,140
Then why did you want to be
on "Human Theater?"

577
00:38:27,740 --> 00:38:32,580
When I asked you to do a show,
you insisted you weren't fit for TV.

578
00:38:33,120 --> 00:38:34,120
Well, that's...

579
00:38:34,750 --> 00:38:37,220
Bucket said something to me.

580
00:38:38,150 --> 00:38:40,390
I want to proudly show them
how I'm doing.

581
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:44,160
How well the children they abandoned
are doing,

582
00:38:44,890 --> 00:38:46,500
how well my kids have grown up...

583
00:38:47,560 --> 00:38:50,000
I just want to proudly show them
what they're missing.

584
00:38:54,270 --> 00:38:55,600
When I heard him say that,

585
00:38:56,510 --> 00:38:59,110
it made me think of my own father.

586
00:39:00,180 --> 00:39:03,580
I can't even film
that vlog with you anymore.

587
00:39:04,310 --> 00:39:07,480
Since a lot of older people watch
"Human Theater,"

588
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:09,520
I thought that wherever he is,

589
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:13,260
my father might happen to see it.

590
00:39:16,860 --> 00:39:18,030
That's right.

591
00:39:19,130 --> 00:39:21,330
That I'm still running our clinic...

592
00:39:22,100 --> 00:39:23,230
even without my father...

593
00:39:24,130 --> 00:39:27,270
That I'm still here in Onjeong,
keeping it going strong.

594
00:39:28,400 --> 00:39:30,410
I guess that's what
I wanted to show him.

595
00:39:33,010 --> 00:39:34,410
I'm sorry, Seong Mi.

596
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:54,460
What did you call me here
to talk about?

597
00:39:56,370 --> 00:39:57,530
To be honest,

598
00:39:59,030 --> 00:40:00,440
I really...

599
00:40:01,340 --> 00:40:04,870
I truly can't stand you.

600
00:40:06,910 --> 00:40:08,210
When I see you,

601
00:40:09,910 --> 00:40:13,150
it just reminds me of
how inadequate I am.

602
00:40:15,750 --> 00:40:16,750
Until I...

603
00:40:17,290 --> 00:40:18,950
became an adult,

604
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:22,020
I lived in an orphanage...

605
00:40:23,130 --> 00:40:24,690
that was run by a convent.

606
00:40:28,260 --> 00:40:30,000
I'm not highly educated,

607
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:32,670
and the only thing I really have...

608
00:40:33,770 --> 00:40:37,740
is this pretty face, as you can see.

609
00:40:39,340 --> 00:40:42,850
Seeing you made me so envious,

610
00:40:45,350 --> 00:40:46,950
and it made me so jealous...

611
00:40:48,280 --> 00:40:49,320
that I've grown to resent you.

612
00:40:51,350 --> 00:40:53,190
So I used what happened to Dong Suk
as an excuse...

613
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:55,520
to try and make you move away.

614
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:59,560
But I realized
that my own selfishness...

615
00:41:00,700 --> 00:41:04,530
shouldn't stand in the way
of what my husband wants.

616
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:09,410
For the way I crossed the line
with my words and actions last time,

617
00:41:10,270 --> 00:41:11,640
I'm not going to beg you...

618
00:41:12,780 --> 00:41:14,440
to forgive me.

619
00:41:15,680 --> 00:41:18,610
Because that would be
selfish of me, too.

620
00:41:20,520 --> 00:41:21,620
I...

621
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,690
I'm asking you with all my heart,
Doctor.

622
00:41:26,990 --> 00:41:28,060
About Dr. Gong...

623
00:41:28,420 --> 00:41:31,460
appearing on "Human Theater"
with Dr. Yang,

624
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:35,360
couldn't you please
give him your permission?

625
00:41:42,810 --> 00:41:44,540
Give me some time to think it over.

626
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:49,140
Of course. Thank you.

627
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:02,860
My parents also passed away
when I was in elementary school,

628
00:42:03,130 --> 00:42:06,760
so I was raised by my grandmother
before I got married at a young age.

629
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:09,470
I was very fortunate...

630
00:42:09,800 --> 00:42:12,200
that my mother-in-law made sure
I could continue my studies.

631
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:15,800
If there's one difference
between us,

632
00:42:16,140 --> 00:42:17,540
it would be our level of education.

633
00:42:19,040 --> 00:42:20,540
If you feel
you've missed out on that,

634
00:42:24,380 --> 00:42:26,180
I don't think it's too late
to change that.

635
00:42:30,920 --> 00:42:32,190
If I'm out of line for saying so,

636
00:42:32,990 --> 00:42:33,990
I apologize.

637
00:42:36,030 --> 00:42:38,690
Thank you for the advice.

638
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:55,510
In that case,

639
00:42:56,380 --> 00:42:59,480
let's all decide this
with a majority vote.

640
00:43:00,680 --> 00:43:03,190
All those who want to move,
raise your hand.

641
00:43:06,090 --> 00:43:08,620
What? It's just you and me, Dad?

642
00:43:09,390 --> 00:43:11,590
It looks that way.

643
00:43:11,990 --> 00:43:14,960
Put your hand down, Gong Jeong Han.
You're not fooling anyone.

644
00:43:15,230 --> 00:43:19,230
But I really want to move! Come on!
I'm serious, I really am!

645
00:43:19,230 --> 00:43:21,700
But Woo Jae,
I thought you wanted to move.

646
00:43:22,140 --> 00:43:24,810
Hey, raise your hand.
Come on, do it.

647
00:43:25,870 --> 00:43:26,910
I'm not going to.

648
00:43:27,580 --> 00:43:28,580
You're the one who told me...

649
00:43:28,980 --> 00:43:30,680
not to live the life
Mom wants for me,

650
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:32,980
but to live the life I want.

651
00:43:33,250 --> 00:43:36,690
Hey, Gong Woo Jae.
Why are you bringing that up now?

652
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:38,650
What are you talking about?

653
00:43:42,590 --> 00:43:44,290
I'm in therapy.

654
00:43:44,590 --> 00:43:45,590
What?

655
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:47,330
- What? What was that?
- What do you mean?

656
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:48,400
Since when?

657
00:43:48,900 --> 00:43:49,900
For a while now.

658
00:43:51,500 --> 00:43:52,900
I'm sure you all saw it coming.

659
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:56,170
I was top of my med school class,
but I still can't get my license.

660
00:43:56,640 --> 00:43:59,980
- It's no surprise I'm not okay.
- Oh, Woo Jae.

661
00:44:00,480 --> 00:44:01,680
I'm sorry, Grandma.

662
00:44:04,480 --> 00:44:05,710
You knew about this?

663
00:44:06,380 --> 00:44:08,780
What? Yes.

664
00:44:09,490 --> 00:44:10,490
Gong Ju Ah, you too?

665
00:44:10,950 --> 00:44:14,190
He said he'd tell you himself
once you were feeling better, Mom.

666
00:44:16,890 --> 00:44:17,890
So...

667
00:44:18,460 --> 00:44:21,260
Woo Jae, are you going to quit,
just like Ju Ah?

668
00:44:23,100 --> 00:44:25,230
Mom, I've dreamed of...

669
00:44:25,330 --> 00:44:27,600
becoming a doctor
ever since I was in your womb.

670
00:44:28,040 --> 00:44:31,540
I want to be a fourth-generation
doctor and run our clinic.

671
00:44:32,810 --> 00:44:33,810
That's my nephew.

672
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:38,350
If you feel that way,
why didn't you say so about moving?

673
00:44:39,880 --> 00:44:42,050
I wanted to come clean
when I had a chance like this.

674
00:44:43,190 --> 00:44:45,890
You're all really making me out
to be the bad guy.

675
00:44:47,020 --> 00:44:48,120
What about you, Dae Han?

676
00:44:48,660 --> 00:44:51,160
Are you really okay with not moving?

677
00:44:52,230 --> 00:44:55,200
Yes. I never wanted to move anyway.

678
00:44:56,870 --> 00:44:57,870
Well, then...

679
00:44:58,870 --> 00:45:02,100
Let's pretend this conversation
never happened...

680
00:45:02,910 --> 00:45:06,310
and officially decide
we're not moving.

681
00:45:07,040 --> 00:45:08,880
Gosh, this is so annoying.

682
00:45:10,580 --> 00:45:12,350
Woo Jae, come with me.

683
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:23,560
- Are you happy now?
- Happy?

684
00:45:24,290 --> 00:45:25,290
What?

685
00:45:26,460 --> 00:45:29,800
Well, yes. I'm happy. So what?
What are you going to do? Goodness.

686
00:45:29,870 --> 00:45:32,300
Yes! I don't have to move!

687
00:45:33,500 --> 00:45:35,700
Uncle, what are you so happy about?

688
00:45:35,770 --> 00:45:39,070
I don't know! I just...
I'm just happy, that's all!

689
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:48,880
Really?

690
00:45:49,720 --> 00:45:54,720
Yes. I'm fine with them not moving.

691
00:45:56,260 --> 00:45:58,630
So Dr. Gong's whole family
has agreed to it?

692
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:03,270
Yes. They had a family meeting.
Not moving and being on the show...

693
00:46:03,330 --> 00:46:05,000
They called
and said yes to all of it.

694
00:46:06,970 --> 00:46:08,170
Thank you so much.

695
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:10,210
I know it couldn't have been easy
for you to ask them.

696
00:46:10,570 --> 00:46:12,210
See, Dad?

697
00:46:12,510 --> 00:46:14,410
In the end, it took my stepmom
to get things done.

698
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:16,450
No, that's not it, Hyun Bin.

699
00:46:16,780 --> 00:46:19,880
It's just like Eun Bin said.
I was blinded by jealousy...

700
00:46:20,080 --> 00:46:22,080
and almost made us
miss out on a great opportunity.

701
00:46:23,120 --> 00:46:25,120
Thank you so much, Stepmom.

702
00:46:25,890 --> 00:46:26,890
Thank you, Se Ri.

703
00:46:27,290 --> 00:46:30,390
For you, I'm going to become
the biggest star in the universe,

704
00:46:30,460 --> 00:46:33,260
and I'll take the country by storm.
I swear.

705
00:46:33,530 --> 00:46:35,660
Yes! Bring it on!

706
00:46:36,570 --> 00:46:38,370
- My goodness.
- How will you take them by storm?

707
00:46:38,430 --> 00:46:40,740
What? I'll just...
I'll blow them all away.

708
00:46:47,880 --> 00:46:50,710
What? Seong Mi.

709
00:46:51,250 --> 00:46:53,250
Did you separate the beds?

710
00:46:54,380 --> 00:46:57,090
Yes. I can't even stand
the sight of you,

711
00:46:57,150 --> 00:46:59,450
and I thought I might just kill you
if we had to touch.

712
00:47:02,420 --> 00:47:03,590
My gosh, but...

713
00:47:03,930 --> 00:47:07,600
I'd completely forgotten this was
two single beds pushed together.

714
00:47:08,530 --> 00:47:11,100
Is that right?
I never forgot. Not once.

715
00:47:12,530 --> 00:47:15,200
But you agreed to everything.

716
00:47:15,270 --> 00:47:17,940
Doesn't that mean
you're not angry anymore?

717
00:47:19,240 --> 00:47:20,310
Don't kid yourself.

718
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:24,310
I knew I couldn't sleep at night
if we moved knowing how you felt.

719
00:47:24,410 --> 00:47:26,150
So it was a decision
I had to force myself to make.

720
00:47:26,750 --> 00:47:29,150
Hey, but if you're going
to be like this,

721
00:47:29,590 --> 00:47:32,190
then I'm the one
who can't sleep peacefully.

722
00:47:33,190 --> 00:47:36,330
You got everything you wanted.
You expect to sleep soundly, too?

723
00:47:37,330 --> 00:47:38,330
Just turn off the light.

724
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:43,470
Right, the light. Turning it off.

725
00:47:48,470 --> 00:47:52,470
Are you sure you'll be okay
with Jeong Han's family not moving?

726
00:47:54,240 --> 00:47:56,950
If you're happy, I'm happy.

727
00:47:58,380 --> 00:47:59,580
But I thought the psychic...

728
00:48:00,020 --> 00:48:01,220
told you
to stay away from the Gongs.

729
00:48:02,120 --> 00:48:03,550
About that...

730
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,560
She actually said
to stay away from round balls.

731
00:48:07,020 --> 00:48:08,020
Round balls?

732
00:48:08,820 --> 00:48:11,460
Like basketballs, golf balls,
and things like that?

733
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:16,030
Yes. I just mistakenly thought
she meant the Gong family.

734
00:48:17,030 --> 00:48:19,030
I'll make sure to dodge any balls
from now on.

735
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:20,970
I'll block them all for you.

736
00:48:23,070 --> 00:48:26,280
This made me realize something
all over again.

737
00:48:26,910 --> 00:48:30,510
That I just can't live without you.

738
00:48:31,810 --> 00:48:32,810
Me too.

739
00:48:33,180 --> 00:48:35,620
I'm never leaving this house again.

740
00:48:46,930 --> 00:48:49,430
To a completely successful event.

741
00:48:49,730 --> 00:48:52,470
Well, I don't think
ours was that great.

742
00:48:52,530 --> 00:48:54,270
Come on,
it all worked out in the end.

743
00:49:00,840 --> 00:49:03,810
There's something I'm curious about.

744
00:49:05,210 --> 00:49:07,720
Are we only dating for one year?

745
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:10,590
- What?
- Well...

746
00:49:10,590 --> 00:49:13,160
You'll go back to Argentina
in a year.

747
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:16,790
That's ridiculous.
How long have you thought this?

748
00:49:16,930 --> 00:49:19,430
Don't tell me you've been thinking
about this ever since I confessed.

749
00:49:20,400 --> 00:49:21,400
Yes.

750
00:49:22,860 --> 00:49:25,570
What? I'm not going anywhere.
I'm planting myself right here.

751
00:49:25,630 --> 00:49:27,240
I wouldn't leave
even if you pushed me out the door.

752
00:49:27,400 --> 00:49:30,640
You're Pacu Nacho Yang,
the global brand director.

753
00:49:31,240 --> 00:49:34,340
Why would a global talent like you
stay here? It's a waste.

754
00:49:34,410 --> 00:49:36,910
Who says you have to be overseas
to be global?

755
00:49:36,910 --> 00:49:39,210
I can just help K-brands go global.

756
00:49:39,550 --> 00:49:43,850
Gosh, I just don't want to hold
a successful director back.

757
00:49:44,190 --> 00:49:47,020
Don't tell me you only want
to date me for a year.

758
00:49:47,320 --> 00:49:48,620
Wouldn't that be for the best?

759
00:49:49,060 --> 00:49:51,260
Besides, there's the whole issue
with our parents.

760
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:54,300
Fine.
Then I'm not dating you at all.

761
00:49:55,730 --> 00:49:58,470
Why do you have to be so dramatic?
Goodness.

762
00:49:58,530 --> 00:50:02,400
My dream is to marry Gong Ju Ah
and live happily ever after.

763
00:50:02,500 --> 00:50:05,840
What? Who says you can? Goodness.

764
00:50:06,270 --> 00:50:08,710
I said we could date.
Who said anything about marriage?

765
00:50:09,110 --> 00:50:10,310
If you're going to get married,

766
00:50:10,310 --> 00:50:12,110
you should date someone
through all four seasons...

767
00:50:12,180 --> 00:50:13,880
before making that kind of decision.

768
00:50:13,950 --> 00:50:17,650
I bet you won't even last one season
before you want to marry me.

769
00:50:18,690 --> 00:50:19,920
We'll see about that.

770
00:50:20,890 --> 00:50:25,360
I'm a marketing expert.
I'm confident I can win anyone over.

771
00:50:25,430 --> 00:50:28,200
I'm pretty sure your family
will fall in love with me.

772
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,600
Oh, no.

773
00:50:29,970 --> 00:50:32,130
My mom's coming
to the office next week.

774
00:50:32,600 --> 00:50:34,640
Now, I'm worried
you're going to pull a stunt.

775
00:50:35,770 --> 00:50:38,310
Wow, you don't know me at all,
do you?

776
00:50:38,770 --> 00:50:41,240
Just wait and see what I do.

777
00:50:42,710 --> 00:50:45,250
And another thing,
I don't want an office romance.

778
00:50:45,750 --> 00:50:47,680
And I hate people
gossiping about me.

779
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:50,390
Yes, I agree with that.

780
00:50:52,320 --> 00:50:55,490
Then should we come up
with some ground rules?

781
00:50:57,190 --> 00:50:59,130
Ground rules
for a secret relationship?

782
00:51:03,430 --> 00:51:04,500
Hold on!

783
00:51:06,400 --> 00:51:07,700
(Arriving at and leaving work)

784
00:51:07,770 --> 00:51:10,240
We should arrive at work
and leave at different times.

785
00:51:10,570 --> 00:51:13,380
The more our paths cross,
the higher the risk of being caught.

786
00:51:13,710 --> 00:51:16,040
And what if we happen
to run into each other?

787
00:51:16,610 --> 00:51:20,520
We maintain a proper distance
and act strictly as colleagues.

788
00:51:22,250 --> 00:51:23,490
(Meetings)

789
00:51:23,550 --> 00:51:26,120
We act strictly professional
during meetings, too.

790
00:51:27,060 --> 00:51:29,520
I trust your presentation
is coming along well?

791
00:51:30,090 --> 00:51:32,230
We ran a rehearsal based on
your revisions from this morning.

792
00:51:32,390 --> 00:51:35,430
The pacing and message delivery
were both clean and effective.

793
00:51:40,340 --> 00:51:42,640
Hey, no googly eyes!

794
00:51:44,040 --> 00:51:45,540
Let's hope for a good outcome.

795
00:51:47,140 --> 00:51:50,350
In the cafeteria,
we must always sit apart.

796
00:51:53,850 --> 00:51:56,350
Did anything interesting happen
over the weekend?

797
00:51:58,020 --> 00:51:59,860
I literally slept all day.

798
00:52:00,490 --> 00:52:02,390
Gosh, I must be getting old.

799
00:52:02,620 --> 00:52:05,830
Be careful.
The VP and Mr. Park will grill us.

800
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,100
So, any progress with Gong Ju Ah?

801
00:52:09,200 --> 00:52:11,570
Aren't you curious about
what happened that night?

802
00:52:11,800 --> 00:52:14,400
Wow, the smoky aroma is amazing.

803
00:52:26,480 --> 00:52:28,450
Oh, that was perfect.

804
00:52:29,250 --> 00:52:31,090
I don't think they suspect a thing,
do you?

805
00:52:31,490 --> 00:52:32,950
Of course not. Not a thing.

806
00:52:33,790 --> 00:52:36,560
The thought that we're dating
would never even cross their minds.

807
00:52:41,360 --> 00:52:42,660
They're definitely dating.

808
00:52:43,060 --> 00:52:44,730
Yes. A hundred percent.

809
00:52:45,470 --> 00:52:46,840
Gosh, but...

810
00:52:47,400 --> 00:52:50,110
It's unclear if it's just a thing,
or if they're officially a couple.

811
00:52:51,740 --> 00:52:54,610
You'll probably find that out
tomorrow.

812
00:52:54,810 --> 00:52:59,610
- Tomorrow? Why?
- I've been debating it all weekend.

813
00:52:59,980 --> 00:53:02,420
About whether I should tell you
or not.

814
00:53:03,690 --> 00:53:05,250
I put my friendship
with Ms. Gong on one side...

815
00:53:06,150 --> 00:53:08,760
and the fate of the Fashion Division
on the other.

816
00:53:09,360 --> 00:53:12,760
And let's just say,
the scales tipped a bit this way.

817
00:53:13,160 --> 00:53:14,600
Gosh, why so serious?

818
00:53:16,530 --> 00:53:19,500
- You know Dr. Han Seong Mi, right?
- Yes.

819
00:53:21,340 --> 00:53:23,040
She's Ms. Gong's mother.

820
00:53:25,370 --> 00:53:26,370
Getting excited?

821
00:53:28,380 --> 00:53:29,380
My goodness.

822
00:53:30,280 --> 00:53:32,580
Am I allowed to have
this much fun at work?

823
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:34,220
My gosh!

824
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:43,660
- What? What's wrong?
- Who is it? Why?

825
00:53:43,730 --> 00:53:45,360
- They're not leaving.
- What?

826
00:53:45,930 --> 00:53:47,730
Who's not leaving?
What are you talking about?

827
00:53:47,930 --> 00:53:50,570
- I mean, the move!
- Really?

828
00:53:50,730 --> 00:53:52,770
But I thought
they'd already decided not to move.

829
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:55,940
Well, they kept going
back and forth about it.

830
00:53:56,240 --> 00:54:00,080
- Wow, that's great news.
- I know, right? I'm so happy.

831
00:54:00,210 --> 00:54:02,240
Yes!

832
00:54:04,380 --> 00:54:05,380
I have to go!

833
00:54:10,850 --> 00:54:11,920
Officer Jung, are you okay?

834
00:54:12,320 --> 00:54:15,360
- Sorry?
- I can hear your heart pounding.

835
00:54:16,790 --> 00:54:20,130
- What do you mean? Goodness.
- Come on.

836
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:22,030
Step aside!
Move, get out of the way.

837
00:54:28,300 --> 00:54:32,170
I thought we already had
an agreement. What happened?

838
00:54:34,810 --> 00:54:37,150
I don't know when,

839
00:54:37,980 --> 00:54:40,520
or if that day will even come,

840
00:54:41,350 --> 00:54:43,790
but if he finds out
the clinic and pharmacy are gone,

841
00:54:44,390 --> 00:54:45,390
Gi Cheol...

842
00:54:46,590 --> 00:54:48,220
would be disappointed.

843
00:54:50,890 --> 00:54:52,730
He's the one who vanished.

844
00:54:54,060 --> 00:54:56,130
What right does he have
to be disappointed?

845
00:54:57,430 --> 00:54:58,430
You're right.

846
00:54:59,330 --> 00:55:01,900
But anyway, here we are,
keeping things going.

847
00:55:04,340 --> 00:55:05,340
Yes.

848
00:55:06,310 --> 00:55:10,150
I know Dae Han and Dong Suk
must be deeply hurt,

849
00:55:11,910 --> 00:55:14,050
but I'm sure they'll heal with time.

850
00:55:14,920 --> 00:55:15,920
Just like we did.

851
00:55:17,290 --> 00:55:18,520
Let's hope so.

852
00:55:41,910 --> 00:55:42,910
What do you want?

853
00:55:43,610 --> 00:55:44,610
You heard, right?

854
00:55:45,310 --> 00:55:46,480
We're not moving.

855
00:55:47,150 --> 00:55:50,550
So? Did you call me out here to see
if your stomach would still hurt?

856
00:55:50,820 --> 00:55:52,790
- Yes.
- And?

857
00:55:53,390 --> 00:55:54,460
I feel fine.

858
00:55:55,320 --> 00:55:56,320
Good for you.

859
00:55:57,560 --> 00:55:59,660
- I'm off.
- Hey, Dong Suk.

860
00:56:00,060 --> 00:56:01,060
What?

861
00:56:01,900 --> 00:56:03,000
What kind of shampoo do you use?

862
00:56:04,270 --> 00:56:06,770
- What?
- That day, I noticed...

863
00:56:07,500 --> 00:56:09,940
your shampoo smelled really nice,
and I was thinking of getting some.

864
00:56:11,870 --> 00:56:13,440
I'll buy some and send it to you.

865
00:56:13,780 --> 00:56:15,680
You could just send me the link.

866
00:56:17,410 --> 00:56:18,510
It's my way of saying thanks.

867
00:56:19,110 --> 00:56:20,120
What?

868
00:56:20,650 --> 00:56:23,250
I remember everything
that happened at the motel now.

869
00:56:24,450 --> 00:56:25,490
For looking out for me...

870
00:56:26,020 --> 00:56:28,060
and being so kind... Thank you.

871
00:56:29,220 --> 00:56:31,430
Then and now,

872
00:56:32,360 --> 00:56:33,830
you've always been a good person.

873
00:56:41,340 --> 00:56:42,340
I'm off.

874
00:56:46,470 --> 00:56:47,480
Okay, bye.

875
00:56:52,210 --> 00:56:54,420
My stomach doesn't hurt,
so why does my heart ache?

876
00:56:56,150 --> 00:56:57,150
What is this feeling?

877
00:56:58,950 --> 00:57:00,790
Is this some kind of
psychosomatic heart condition?

878
00:57:01,920 --> 00:57:03,490
- Get home safe.
- Okay.

879
00:57:03,490 --> 00:57:05,690
- And be sure to take your medicine.
- I will. Thank you.

880
00:57:05,760 --> 00:57:06,800
All right, take care.

881
00:57:08,160 --> 00:57:11,270
Hey. I heard
Seong Mi gave you the okay.

882
00:57:11,630 --> 00:57:13,500
So you're doing
"Human Theater," right?

883
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:15,600
Thank you, my friend.

884
00:57:16,810 --> 00:57:18,340
"My friend," my foot.

885
00:57:19,210 --> 00:57:21,680
"Human Theater?" What's that?
Something to eat?

886
00:57:21,740 --> 00:57:25,810
Hey, I knew you'd be like this,
so I wrote down a few more quotes.

887
00:57:27,280 --> 00:57:30,190
What's this?
"How can a person change so much?"

888
00:57:30,790 --> 00:57:32,820
"Nothing's gone right
since I met you?"

889
00:57:33,420 --> 00:57:35,420
The feeling is mutual, you jerk.

890
00:57:36,190 --> 00:57:37,830
Hey, come on. Cut me some slack.

891
00:57:42,200 --> 00:57:44,630
You barely ate all weekend,
didn't you?

892
00:57:45,270 --> 00:57:47,700
I'll make the webfoot octopus
for dinner tonight.

893
00:57:48,700 --> 00:57:50,040
I'm so sorry, Father.

894
00:57:52,610 --> 00:57:53,640
Listen.

895
00:57:55,040 --> 00:57:56,950
This is the last meal
you'll be making for me.

896
00:57:57,880 --> 00:58:01,380
- What?
- From now on, hire a housekeeper.

897
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:04,250
I won't work you like this anymore.

898
00:58:04,750 --> 00:58:05,750
But...

899
00:58:06,290 --> 00:58:10,690
I like taking care of a big family,
since I grew up without my own.

900
00:58:10,760 --> 00:58:12,760
I told you that when I got married.

901
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:20,840
You were probably just being polite
to your lonely old father-in-law.

902
00:58:21,540 --> 00:58:24,570
And this foolish old man
took you at your word and...

903
00:58:25,470 --> 00:58:26,510
gave you a hard time.

904
00:58:27,380 --> 00:58:30,680
Hire help. Do as I say. From now on,

905
00:58:31,550 --> 00:58:32,710
let's take better care of you.

906
00:58:33,780 --> 00:58:36,120
Then what am I supposed to do?

907
00:58:38,620 --> 00:58:42,120
I've secretly felt bad about
only helping Dong Suk open her shop.

908
00:58:42,990 --> 00:58:44,230
You should open one, too.

909
00:58:47,900 --> 00:58:50,630
Actually, Father, instead of that,

910
00:58:51,600 --> 00:58:53,030
there's something else
I'd like to ask.

911
00:58:53,470 --> 00:58:54,540
Sure.

912
00:58:55,270 --> 00:58:58,010
I'd like to go back to school.

913
00:58:59,010 --> 00:59:00,010
School?

914
00:59:00,780 --> 00:59:01,780
Yes.

915
00:59:02,080 --> 00:59:05,810
My credentials are what's keeping
my husband from a council seat.

916
00:59:06,310 --> 00:59:08,450
I really want to study hard.

917
00:59:08,750 --> 00:59:10,750
I was a pretty good student,
you know.

918
00:59:12,020 --> 00:59:13,420
I'm sure you were.

919
00:59:15,020 --> 00:59:17,230
I'll give you my full support.

920
00:59:19,330 --> 00:59:23,130
I know I can never be
like Dr. Han Seong Mi.

921
00:59:23,870 --> 00:59:27,800
I refuse to just be a wife
by his side, consumed with jealousy.

922
00:59:33,310 --> 00:59:36,210
(Taehan)

923
00:59:46,090 --> 00:59:47,290
Welcome, Doctor.

924
00:59:48,160 --> 00:59:50,120
My, what a grand welcome.

925
00:59:52,260 --> 00:59:55,230
This is the Vice President
of Taehan Group.

926
00:59:56,400 --> 00:59:59,270
It's an honor, Doctor.
I'm Hwangbo Hye Su.

927
00:59:59,400 --> 01:00:02,670
I hope I can pull my weight
as the brand's model.

928
01:00:03,140 --> 01:00:04,310
We'll do our best to support you.

929
01:00:05,310 --> 01:00:08,110
This is Park Jun Hyeok
and Gong Ju Ah.

930
01:00:12,580 --> 01:00:13,820
It's a pleasure to be
working with you.

931
01:00:14,450 --> 01:00:17,150
- I'm a huge fan, Doctor.
- Thank you.

932
01:00:19,620 --> 01:00:23,890
She's our head designer
and the jewel of our Taehan Fashion.

933
01:00:27,800 --> 01:00:30,200
A pleasure to meet you,
Ms. Gong Ju Ah.

934
01:00:32,300 --> 01:00:34,170
I look forward to working with you,
Doctor.

935
01:00:47,650 --> 01:00:48,650
Here, Woo Jae.

936
01:00:49,820 --> 01:00:51,250
- Eun Bin.
- Yes?

937
01:00:51,320 --> 01:00:53,350
I thought you said you'd start
listening to your stepmom.

938
01:00:53,690 --> 01:00:56,690
If you keep following me like this,
I bet your stepmom will be furious.

939
01:00:56,920 --> 01:00:59,160
Hey, if you're taking a break
from studying,

940
01:00:59,160 --> 01:01:00,290
why not go on a trip
with me instead?

941
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:02,100
What's all this about
getting a part-time job?

942
01:01:02,360 --> 01:01:04,770
I told you I'd earn money
and support you.

943
01:01:04,830 --> 01:01:05,900
Don't be...

944
01:01:06,300 --> 01:01:09,470
- ridiculous.
- Why? Am I wrong?

945
01:01:10,670 --> 01:01:12,610
I just want different experiences,
that's all.

946
01:01:12,770 --> 01:01:16,740
Still, a barbecue joint?
You should be tutoring or something.

947
01:01:17,080 --> 01:01:18,180
Tutor me.

948
01:01:18,650 --> 01:01:19,950
- It's time.
- What?

949
01:01:19,950 --> 01:01:21,980
- I have to go.
- Wait.

950
01:01:25,250 --> 01:01:26,250
Seriously.

951
01:01:35,130 --> 01:01:36,160
But...

952
01:01:36,830 --> 01:01:39,100
I'm not the only one doing well,
am I, Sister?

953
01:01:40,230 --> 01:01:42,400
Veronica is doing very well, too.

954
01:01:49,480 --> 01:01:50,480
This...

955
01:01:51,680 --> 01:01:53,310
May I take it with me?

956
01:01:54,080 --> 01:01:55,920
Are you sure you'll be okay?

957
01:01:57,990 --> 01:01:59,750
This is all I have left.

958
01:02:01,360 --> 01:02:02,860
So I'm always thinking about it.

959
01:02:05,830 --> 01:02:07,360
I want to keep it with me now.

960
01:02:09,300 --> 01:02:12,430
I'll pray that He watches over you.

961
01:02:28,620 --> 01:02:30,790
(Damga Charcoal Grill,
Onjeong Market)

962
01:02:30,850 --> 01:02:31,990
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

963
01:02:32,050 --> 01:02:33,290
Enjoy your meal.

964
01:02:33,620 --> 01:02:34,620
Thank you.

965
01:02:35,420 --> 01:02:36,420
Welcome.

966
01:02:41,400 --> 01:02:42,500
You're the one from...

967
01:02:43,200 --> 01:02:45,430
- Hello.
- Hello.

968
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:47,900
What? You know her?

969
01:02:49,040 --> 01:02:53,270
- You lost that pendant, right?
- Yes. Do you happen to have it?

970
01:02:53,610 --> 01:02:54,740
Just a moment.

971
01:02:55,480 --> 01:02:56,510
Yes, here it is.

972
01:03:07,160 --> 01:03:08,160
Give that back, please.

973
01:03:10,530 --> 01:03:11,590
It's mine.

974
01:04:24,770 --> 01:04:27,570
(Recipe for Love)

975
01:04:27,640 --> 01:04:29,300
Ju Ah has a boyfriend?

976
01:04:29,370 --> 01:04:32,840
- I think he's a coworker, so watch.
- Is it Jun Hyeok?

977
01:04:33,210 --> 01:04:34,210
What's this?

978
01:04:35,880 --> 01:04:39,480
Director Yang is someone
who gets whatever he wants.

979
01:04:39,580 --> 01:04:43,050
- He's one of the best directors.
- He sounds very impressive.

980
01:04:44,150 --> 01:04:47,290
Here's the golf coach.
Looks like it's a couples' lesson.

981
01:04:47,360 --> 01:04:49,420
This is your chance.
Go score some points with Seong Mi.

982
01:04:49,490 --> 01:04:51,290
Hey, how many times
do I have to tell you?

983
01:04:51,360 --> 01:04:54,930
- Are you deaf? You fool!
- With me...

984
01:04:55,200 --> 01:04:56,200
Go on, say it.

985
01:04:56,760 --> 01:04:59,070
With me...
